arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
5.50 m north south -by- 1.85 m east west.

Locus 36 is the layer of soil and collapse below the main level of collapse (Locus 3) in the “southwest room.” It is a coarse sandy soil (Munsell 7.5 YR 3/2 dark brown) with significant plaster and ash inclusions, along with collapsed ashlars and rubble. This locus resembles the collapse layer in the rest of the bath complex, and so is phased with those loci to the main collapse period – Stage 7.
Dark brown soil and collapse in the “southwest room”
